Picture of a motion picture, actress Bunny Blake. A camera dolly with aspiring career goals, to be forefront and center on the biggest screen she can find. But her taste in roles are quite exclusive, you see: behind the clapperboard she prefers to clap a broad, and prefers to spend a movie's Abbies in bed with Abbys. Every film score is a score, a match cut in costume design.

And yet, despite her clear bias, the male gaze persists. Stalker vision growing increasingly close, encroaching on the ambient light of her career. If she wants to finally rid herself of this forced perspective, she'll need to find the heart of the obsession — one Mr. Morris — and wipe it out. She'll only get one shot to cut him off.

Lights, camera, //action//: a filmography designed only for Broadway — not those who reside within the Boundryless Confines.

