The position of Vice President of the United States is a big chair to fill. With the power it incurs, one can imagine it is a coveted seat on Capitol Hill, and James David Vance knows this all too well. You see, our resident incumbent has never tabled an offer he could afford to take, and has never been afraid to look behind the curtain at what lies bed, bath, and beyond. There is nothing the Vice President wouldn't do to pad his own pockets.

Until this moment, Mr. Vance has not racked up a noticeable debt on his karmatic credit card. But even if he can pay his late fees, there are many who seek to lampshade his less-than-scrupulous past, and with it, sink his off-brand reputation. For in this particular instance, the glove //does// fit, and there is not much he can do to cushion the fall.

He has made his king-sized bed — and now Mr. Vance must lie in it. For hell hath no fury like a sofa's scorn... in the endless aisles of the Boundryless Confines.

