Her name is Haddaway, first name unimportant, age 59. A widow-turned-worker who pines for days long gone, who wishes to hark back to an era before everything went so astray. What she is looking for is a sign; a hope against hope that she will be hurt no more. And unfortunately for her, that sign may come, in an imperceptible form that whisks her away long after the daydream departs.

The year? 1993. At least, that's the year for now. Because what Mrs. Haddaway is about to witness is a mausoleum of madness, a place of shadow and dust, occupied by a raving lunatic with a warped perception of even the most fundamental axioms of reality. She must come to a final deduction and determine a way out of their collective predicament, or spend an eternity losing herself. A terrifying ordeal; find it filed under "A" for "Alternative", down the dancing stretch of road that leads right into the heart of the Boundryless Confines.

