This is Mr. White, trapped in a museum long past closing time of the early morning of September 21st, 1978. It has been September 21st, 1978 for several years. He has been wandering these aching, dusting halls trying to find the answer to his predicament amongst the bones and diagrams, but a solution seems ever-elusive. Mr. White has no need to eat, to drink, to sleep; and, he largely suspects, he's begun to go mad from the isolation, the only companions he has being the crumbling statues of years long gone and the dusty mannequins lining the walls.

In just a moment, we will see Mr. White encounter something new: someone else who has found themselves trapped in this mausoleum of madness, much like him. But this will only leave him with more questions, as he begins to doubt the authenticity of facts he's long established. Find it filed under "M" for "Mnemosyne", and mind the gap as you cross into... the Boundryless Confines.

