Shamed. Forgotten. Forsaken. In a society of sexual liberation, it can seem apocryphal to acknowledge the reality that not all so-called consensual actions are as moral as they may purport. For those under that veil — those who have been dealt a bad hand in the game called life — this reality is ever-present, even if equally unacknowledgeable. That golden word "yes", the abstract notion of approval, is not always dealt in the most objective contexts. And those unfortunate enough to fall for this trap often find themselves at the mercy of the very people who claim to defend them.

Pay close attention, for this tale involves more pragmatic than semantic definition, and a failure to perceive between the lines can lead one to miss the forest for the trees. There is blood flowing beneath our feet, and unless it is scooped up to congeal, it will forever flow off the edges of the Earth, never to be seen again. Flowing deep into the darkest pits... of the Boundryless Confines.

