High above the Earth, far beyond the clouds, a woman waits in yearning. For eons, Luna has rest her watchful gaze upon the human race, waiting patiently. She spends her endless time collecting those in her orbit, seeking one who may be able to totally eclipse her. And on one winter evening above North America in 1962, she finds him: an arm-strong man with a promising career, a handsome smile, and a gravitational presence that helplessly pulls her towards him. 

All she will need to do is convince him to fly sky high, Sea her Tranquility, and land his Eagle. One giant leap for mankind, for one small step from a man. Blink, and you'll miss it, as this sort of tale only ever happens once in a blue moon, above the Boundryless Confines.

