The alarms you hear are a sign of the end times. The first Horseman of the Apocalypse is now galloping upon the Earth, but it is neither Conquest nor Pestilence. Rather, it takes the form of an imperceptible blur, a white-hot streak flung across the heavens in an arch, ready to reduce mankind to its primal state once more. 

You see, an affair that will kill millions in mere minutes is about to unfold. For the three most powerful nations in the world are right now trapped in a triangle of one night stands and zero day dates, and as the clock ticks ever closer to the sweet release of a doomsday midnight, fingers twitch above those big red buttons in Washington, waiting for the final climax of the human experience. And if it comes — //when// it comes — the shockwaves will reverberate throughout the cosmos in one final, guttural scream. A scream that will leave humanity gasping for precious air that no longer exists, air that has long since departed... to the Boundryless Confines.

