It is said that behind every great man there is an equally great woman. This aphorism is much more than a metaphor for Mr. Elo Bannister, who has been blessed with a wife who can not only match his impeccable wits, but also utterly capture his heart. They are a team that cannot be rivaled; a power couple of domination that counterplays their competition so swiftly that they don't even have time to say the word "checkmate".

What Mr. Bannister does not know yet is that he is merely a pawn in a grander scheme; a piece being moved across a board by a higher power. For his wife, Mrs. Caïssa Bannister, has much grander ambitions than merely being a queen to his king. This was not a decision that could be made //en passant//, and no matter what other gambit he has prepared, Elo will soon learn the hard way that a king cannot mate. A sevenfold repetition that will at best leave him with a dead draw... in the highest stakes game of chess throughout the growing expanse of the Boundryless Confines.

