[[div style="color: #222;"]]
And thus, the blinds are drawn, the curtains closed, and the performance long ended. All that remains of the human race is the sodden earth, saturated with the fats of slaughtered animals and the blood of men. There is no point to the carnage, no reason for the madness. One may find that there never was one to begin with. 

By this point, our friend Adam has long since abandonded the thought of civilization. There is nothing left of the human race besides him — or so he believes. For while humanity's eyes may be shutting for the final time, Adam's gaze remains lifted to heaven, and the once dark future  will soon have a light at the end of the tunnel. And although the blind may lead the blind, and eye for an eye will only lead to eternal darkness... the ever-growing, all-encompassing, totally-consuming darkness... of the Boundryless Confines.

